<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1921-01-25T23:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1921-01-25T23:00:00-05:00" n="374" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d374">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.74/60: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Crane</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-01-26T12:00:00+08:00"><hi rend="italic">January 26,
                                        1921—noon</hi></date>.<lb/>[Received January 27—2:24
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>60. My 41, January 20, 2 p.m. Ministry of Communications informs me
                            Japanese Minister has made representations to Foreign Office on the
                            basis Mitsui contract.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Crane</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>